        "NOTE: An accuracy can be assigned to a magnitude using the property has accuracy.",
        "DEFINITION: The amount of a measurable characteristic (aspect).",
        "EXAMPLE: A model of car could have a wheelbase of 113.2 inches. In this example, the aspect is wheelbase, the unit of measure is inch, and the numeric value is 113.2."
